# Approval/snapshot files are machine-generated byte-for-byte outputs that
# tests compare against at runtime. Prettier reformatting them (tabs vs
# spaces, key ordering) breaks the equality check and makes the suite flaky.
# Humans review these via the diff at write-time, not the formatter on commit.
**/__snapshots__/**

# Visual regression fixtures are generated at test time and consumed by
# pixel-diff assertions. Reformatting them changes byte output and trips
# the diff. Treated the same as snapshot files above.
**/tests/visual/fixtures/**

# Vendored Obsidian community themes, copied verbatim for the preview tool's
# theme picker. They are third-party artifacts we don't author, and some trip
# Prettier's CSS parser. Keep them byte-for-byte as shipped upstream.
tools/obsidian-preview/public/themes/**
